cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on the task of semantic segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) for hair and facial skin segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses the color moment algorithm to extract color features, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes an efficient segmentation method, which involves trade-offs between speed and performance, indicating that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the unsatisfactory accuracy of skin tones classification, which suggests that it may belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with facial skin tones grading, which may fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
